n
\lim_{n\to \infty} \prod_{k=1}^n \left(1+\frac an + \frac {bk}{n^2}\right) = e^{a + b/2}.
\sum_{k=1}^n =\frac{n(n+1)}{2}\sim \frac{n^2}{2}
\prod_{k=1}^n \left(1+\frac an + \frac {bk}{n^2}\right) \sim  \left(1+\frac an + \frac {b}{2n}\right)^n.
\lim_{n\to \infty}  \left(1+\frac an + \frac {b}{2n}\right)^n =e^{a+\frac{b}{2}}.
